== Mashed Sweet Potato ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Peel and cut the @sweet potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Strip the @thyme{1/2%ounce} from the sprigs and roughly chop the leaves (you'll want about 1 teaspoon).

Place the sweet potato cubes in the pot of water, bring to a boil, and cook for ~{10-15%minutes}, until fork-tender. Drain and return to the same pot.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

Toss the @broccoli florets{16%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until slightly crispy.

== Pan-Seared Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.

Season the @chicken breasts{24%ounce} on all sides with salt and pepper. Add the chicken to the pan for ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until browned but not yet cooked through.

Transfer to the baking sheet in the oven to finish cooking for ~{5%minutes}. Once removed from the oven, let the chicken rest for ~{5%minutes} before serving.

== Creamy Thyme Sauce ==

Add the thyme and a splash of water to the pan over medium heat. Scrape up the browned bits from the bottom of the pan.

Add the @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, then simmer until thickened and reduced by half.

Remove the pan from the heat, then stir in the @sour cream{2%ounce}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Finish and Serve ==

Mash the sweet potatoes with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until smooth.

Stir in @butter{2%tablespoon} and season to taste with salt and pepper. Reheat over medium heat, if necessary.

Thinly slice the pan-seared chicken and serve alongside the roasted broccoli and mashed sweet potato. Drizzle the creamy thyme sauce over top and enjoy!